<title>Snakes and spirits of the dead</title>
<summary>People become spirits when they die. A dead man has a mere spirit as well as an other which is a snake. Spirit-animals live near graves. If a man dies he becomes a snake. Men also become snakes when bitten by them (&apos;and his snake is a spirit&apos;). If a woman dies she becomes a mere spirit unless she dies of a snakebite in which case she becomes a snake. Mere spirits go away.</summary><comments>1) See also <i>A snake found near a grave</i> and <i>A certain snake, which, by lying upon its back, announces a death in the family; and must not, in these circumstances, be killed</i>, 2) This story is found in Book XI &amp; XII-12</comments><date>Ocober 1881</date><storypages>9956v-9957v</storypages><category>Custom and daily life</category><author>!nanni (XI)</author><keyword><kw>death</kw><subkw>snakes and spirits of the dead</subkw></keyword>
